    <title>Standard View Helper Library</title>

    <para>Should be autogenerated from the tags.</para>
<section><title>actionLink</title><para>Link-generation view helper.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Defaults</title><programlisting>&lt;f:actionLink&gt;some link&lt;/f:actionLink&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;a href="currentpackage/currentcontroller"&gt;some link&lt;/a&gt;</para><para>(depending on routing setup and current package/controller/action)</para><example><title>Additional arguments</title><programlisting>&lt;f:actionLink action="myAction" controller="MyController" package="MyPackage" subpackage="MySubpackage" arguments="{key1: 'value1', key2: 'value2'}"&gt;some link&lt;/f:actionLink&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;a href="mypackage/mycontroller/mysubpackage/myaction?key1=value1&amp;key2=value2"&gt;some link&lt;/a&gt;</para><para>(depending on routing setup)</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>action</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of target action.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>controller</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of target controller. Defaults to current controller.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>package</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of target package</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>subpackage</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of target subpackage</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>arguments</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Associative array of all URL arguments which should be appended</entry></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>base</title><para>View helper which creates a &lt;base href="..."&gt;&lt;/base&gt; tag.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:base /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;base href="http://yourdomain.tld/"&gt;&lt;/base&gt;</para><para>(depending on your domain)</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><para>No arguments defined.</para></section></section><section><title>else</title><para>"ELSE" -&gt; only has an effect inside of "IF". See If-ViewHelper for documentation.</para><section><title>Arguments</title><para>No arguments defined.</para></section></section><section><title>for</title><para>Loop view helper</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Simple</title><programlisting>&lt;f:for each="{0:1, 1:2, 2:3, 3:4}" as="foo"&gt;{foo}&lt;/f:for&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>1234</para><example><title>Output array key</title><programlisting>&lt;ul&gt;
   &lt;f:for each="{fruit1: 'apple', fruit2: 'pear', fruit3: 'banana', fruit4: 'cherry'}" as="fruit" key="label"&gt;
     &lt;li&gt;{label}: {fruit}&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;/f:for&gt;
 &lt;/ul&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;ul&gt;</para><para>&lt;li&gt;fruit1: apple&lt;/li&gt;</para><para>&lt;li&gt;fruit2: pear&lt;/li&gt;</para><para>&lt;li&gt;fruit3: banana&lt;/li&gt;</para><para>&lt;li&gt;fruit4: cherry&lt;/li&gt;</para><para>&lt;/ul&gt;</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>each</entry><entry>array</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The array to be iterated over</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>as</entry><entry>string</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The name of the iteration variable</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>key</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>The name of the variable to store the current array key</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form</title><para>Form view helper. Generates a &lt;form&gt; Tag.</para><section><title>Basic usage</title><para>Use &lt;f:form&gt; to output an HTML &lt;form&gt; tag which is targeted at the specified action, in the current controller and package.</para><para>It will submit the form data via a POST request. If you want to change this, use method="get" as an argument.</para><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:form action="..."&gt;...&lt;/f:form&gt;</programlisting></example></section><section><title>A complex form with a specified encoding type</title><example><title>Form with enctype set</title><programlisting>&lt;f:form action=".." controller="..." package="..." enctype="multipart/form-data"&gt;...&lt;/f:form&gt;</programlisting></example></section><section><title>A Form which should render a domain object</title><example><title>Binding a domain object to a form</title><programlisting>&lt;f:form action="..." name="customer" object="{customer}"&gt;
   &lt;f:form.hidden property="id" /&gt;
   &lt;f:form.textbox property="name" /&gt;
 &lt;/f:form&gt;</programlisting></example><para>This automatically inserts the value of {customer.name} inside the textbox and adjusts the name of the textbox accordingly.</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>action</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>name of action to call</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>controller</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>name of controller to call the current action on</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>package</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>name target package</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>subpackage</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>target subpackage</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>arguments</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>name of action to call Associative array of all URL arguments which should be appended to the action URI.</entry></row><row><entry>object</entry><entry>mixed</entry><entry></entry><entry>Object to use for the form. Use in conjunction with the "property" attribute on the sub tags</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>enctype</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>MIME type with which the form is submitted</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>method</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Transfer type (GET or POST)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of form</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>onreset</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>JavaScript: On reset of the form</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>onsubmit</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>JavaScript: On submit of the form</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form.hidden</title><para>Renders an &lt;input type="hidden" ...&gt; tag.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:hidden name="myHiddenValue" value="42" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;input type="hidden" name="myHiddenValue" value="42" /&gt;</para><para>You can also use the "property" attribute if you have bound an object to the form.</para><para>See &lt;f:form&gt; for more documentation.</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>value</entry><entry>mixed</entry><entry></entry><entry>Value of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>property</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of Object Property. If used in conjunction with &lt;f3:form object="..."&gt;, "name" and "value" properties will be ignored.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form.select</title><para>This view helper generates a &lt;select&gt; dropdown list for the use with a form.</para><section><title>Basic usage</title><para>The most straightforward way is to supply an associative array as the "options" parameter.</para><para>The array key is used as option key, and the value is used as human-readable name.</para><example><title>Basic usage</title><programlisting>&lt;f3:form.select name="paymentOptions" options="{payPal: 'PayPal International Services', visa: 'VISA Card'}" /&gt;</programlisting></example></section><section><title>Pre-select a value</title><para>To pre-select a value, set "selectedValue" to the option key which should be selected.</para><example><title>Default value</title><programlisting>&lt;f3:form.select name="paymentOptions" options="{payPal: 'PayPal International Services', visa: 'VISA Card'}" selectedValue="visa" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Generates a dropdown box like above, except that "VISA Card" is selected.</para><para>If the select box is a multi-select box (multiple="true"), then "selectedValue" can be an array as well.</para></section><section><title>Usage on domain objects</title><para>If you want to output domain objects, you can just pass them as array into the "options" parameter.</para><para>To define what domain object value should be used as option key, use the "optionValueField" variable. Same goes for optionLabelField.</para><para>If the optionValueField variable is set, the getter named after that value is used to retrieve the option key.</para><para>If the optionLabelField variable is set, the getter named after that value is used to retrieve the option value.</para><example><title>Domain objects</title><programlisting>&lt;f3:form.select name="users" options="{userArray}" optionValueField="id" optionLabelField="firstName" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>In the above example, the userArray is an array of "User" domain objects, with no array key specified.</para><para>So, in the above example, the method $user-&gt;getId() is called to retrieve the key, and $user-&gt;getFirstName() to retrieve the displayed value of each entry.</para><para>The "selectedValue" property now expects a domain object, and tests for object equivalence.</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>value</entry><entry>mixed</entry><entry></entry><entry>Value of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>property</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of Object Property. If used in conjunction with &lt;f3:form object="..."&gt;, "name" and "value" properties will be ignored.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>multiple</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>if set, multiple select field</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>size</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Size of input field</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>options</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Associative array with internal IDs as key, and the values are displayed in the select box</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>optionValueField</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>If specified, will call the appropriate getter on each object to determine the value.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>optionLabelField</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>If specified, will call the appropriate getter on each object to determine the label.</entry><entry/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form.submit</title><para>Creates a submit button.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Defaults</title><programlisting>&lt;f:submit value="Send Mail" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;input type="submit" /&gt;</para><example><title>Dummy content for template preview</title><programlisting>&lt;f:submit name="mySubmit" value="Send Mail"&gt;&lt;button&gt;dummy button&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/f:submit&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;input type="submit" name="mySubmit" value="Send Mail" /&gt;</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of submit tag</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>value</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Value of submit tag</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form.textarea</title><para>Textarea view helper.</para><para>The value of the text area needs to be set via the "value" attribute, as with all other form ViewHelpers.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:textarea name="myTextArea" value="This is shown inside the textarea" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;textarea name="myTextArea"&gt;This is shown inside the textarea&lt;/textarea&gt;</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>value</entry><entry>mixed</entry><entry></entry><entry>Value of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>property</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of Object Property. If used in conjunction with &lt;f3:form object="..."&gt;, "name" and "value" properties will be ignored.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>rows</entry><entry>int</entry><entry></entry><entry>The number of rows of a text area</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>cols</entry><entry>int</entry><entry></entry><entry>The number of columns of a text area</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form.textbox</title><para>View Helper which creates a simple Text Box (&lt;input type="text"&gt;).</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:textbox name="myTextBox" value="default value" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;input type="text" name="myTextBox" value="default value" /&gt;</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>value</entry><entry>mixed</entry><entry></entry><entry>Value of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>property</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of Object Property. If used in conjunction with &lt;f3:form object="..."&gt;, "name" and "value" properties will be ignored.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>form.upload</title><para>A view helper which generates an &lt;input type="file"&gt; HTML element.</para><para>Make sure to set enctype="multipart/form-data" on the form!</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:upload name="file" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;input type="file" name="file" /&gt;</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>value</entry><entry>mixed</entry><entry></entry><entry>Value of input tag</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>property</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of Object Property. If used in conjunction with &lt;f3:form object="..."&gt;, "name" and "value" properties will be ignored.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>class</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>CSS class(es) for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>dir</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Text direction for this HTML element. Allowed strings: "ltr" (left to right), "rtl" (right to left)</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>id</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Unique (in this file) identifier for this HTML element.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>lang</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Language for this element. Use short names specified in RFC 1766</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>style</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Individual CSS styles for this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>title</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Tooltip text of element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>accesskey</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Keyboard shortcut to access this element</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>tabindex</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry></entry><entry>Specifies the tab order of this element</entry><entry></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>format.crop</title><para>Use this view helper to crop the text between its opening and closing tags.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Defaults</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.crop maxCharacters="10"&gt;This is some very long text&lt;/f:format.crop&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>This is so...</para><example><title>Custom suffix</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.crop maxCharacters="17" append=" [more]"&gt;This is some very long text&lt;/f:format.crop&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>This is some very [more]</para><para>WARNING: This tag does NOT handle tags currently.</para><para>WARNING: This tag doesn't care about multibyte charsets currently.</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>maxCharacters</entry><entry>integer</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>Place where to truncate the string</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>append</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>What to append, if truncation happened</entry><entry>...</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>format.currency</title><para>Formats a given float to a currency representation.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Defaults</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.currency value="123.456" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>123,46</para><example><title>All parameters</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.currency value="54321.0" currencySign="$" decimalSeparator="." thousandsSeparator="," /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>54,321.00 $</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>value</entry><entry>float</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The number being formatted.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>currencySign</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>(optional) The currency sign, eg $ or €.</entry><entry></entry></row><row><entry>decimalSeparator</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>(optional) The separator for the decimal point.</entry><entry>,</entry></row><row><entry>thousandsSeparator</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>(optional) The thousands separator.</entry><entry>.</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>format.date</title><para>Formats a \DateTime object.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Defaults</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.date date="{dateObject}" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>1980-12-13</para><para>(depending on the current date)</para><example><title>Custom date format</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.date date="{dateObject}" format="H:i" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>01:23</para><para>(depending on the current time)</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>date</entry><entry>DateTime</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The DateTime object to format</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>format</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Format String which is taken to format the Date/Time</entry><entry>Y-m-d</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>format.htmlEscape</title><para>A view helper for escaping HTML. Any HTML character in the body of this tag will</para><para>be escaped to an HTML entity.</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Example</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.htmlEscape&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will be &lt;em&gt;escaped&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/f:format.htmlEscape&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>&lt;p&gt;This will be &lt;em&gt;escaped&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><para>No arguments defined.</para></section></section><section><title>format.nl2br</title><para>Wrapper for PHPs nl2br function.</para><section><title>Arguments</title><para>No arguments defined.</para></section></section><section><title>format.number</title><para>Formats a number with custom precision, decimal point and grouped thousands.</para><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>value</entry><entry>float</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The value to format</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>decimals</entry><entry>int</entry><entry></entry><entry>The number of digits after the decimal point</entry><entry>2</entry></row><row><entry>decimalSeparator</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>The decimal point character</entry><entry>.</entry></row><row><entry>thousandsSeparator</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>The character for grouping the thousand digits</entry><entry>,</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>format.printf</title><para>A view helper for formatting values with printf. Either supply an array for</para><para>the arguments or a single value.</para><para>See http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.sprintf.php</para><section><title>Examples</title><example><title>Scientific notation</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.printf format="%.3e" arguments="{number : 362525200}" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>3.625e+8</para><example><title>Argument swapping</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.printf format="%2$s is great, TYPO%1$d too. Yes, TYPO%1$d is great and so is %2$s!" arguments="{0: 3,1: 'Kasper'}" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>Kasper is great, TYPO3 too. Yes, TYPO3 is great and so is Kasper!</para><example><title>Single argument</title><programlisting>&lt;f:format.printf format="We love %s" arguments="{1:'TYPO3'}" /&gt;</programlisting></example><para>Output:</para><para>We love TYPO3</para></section><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>format</entry><entry>string</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The printf format string</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>arguments</entry><entry>array</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>The arguments for vsprintf</entry><entry/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>if</title><para>This view helper implements an if/else condition.</para><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>condition</entry><entry>boolean</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>View helper condition</entry><entry/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>layout</title><para>With this tag, you can select a layout to be used.</para><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>name</entry><entry>string</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>Name of layout to use. If none given, "default" is used.</entry><entry/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></section><section><title>link</title><para>Link-generation view helper</para><section><title>Arguments</title><table><title>Arguments</title><tgroup cols="4"><thead><row><entry>Name</entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Required</entry><entry>Description</entry><entry>Default</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>additionalAttributes</entry><entry>array</entry><entry></entry><entry>Additional tag attributes. They will be added directly to the resulting HTML tag.</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>action</entry><entry>string</entry><entry>1</entry><entry>Name of action where the link points to</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>controller</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of controller where the link points to</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>package</entry><entry>string</entry><entry></entry><entry>Name of package where the link points to</entry><entry/></row><row><entry>subpacka